casebody.data:
JUNE, 1925.

Alexandro Estrado v. The State. No. 9526. Delivered June 17, 1925. A. B. Cowan, for appellant. Tom Garrard, State’s Attorney, and Grover C. Morris, Assistant State’s Attorney, for the State. HAWKINS, Judge.

Conviction is for assault with intent to murder. Punishment, two years in the penitentiary.

The record contains neither statement of facts nor bills of exception. Nothing is presented for review.

The judgment is affirmed.

Affirmed.
